entities.name: Yao
entities.description: Yao is a backend service that can be utilized for building applications.

entities.name: Mobile App Client
entities.description: Mobile App Client refers to the client-side application for mobile devices, which can be developed natively or using a mobile app development framework.

entities.name: SUI template engine
entities.description: SUI template engine is a new feature introduced in Yao 0.10.4 for building web pages, though still experimental.

entities.name: REST API
entities.description: REST API is a method for connecting frontend frameworks like React or Vue to Yao.

entities.name: TypeScript
entities.description: TypeScript is the recommended language for writing custom processes in Yao, running in the V8 engine.

entities.name: V8 engine
entities.description: V8 engine is the JavaScript engine that runs TypeScript processes in Yao.

entities.name: Go
entities.description: Go is a programming language recommended for high-performance processes in Yao, faster than TypeScript.

entities.name: Yao Process
entities.description: A Process in Yao is an atomic function that runs in the Yao Runtime, with hundreds of internal processes available.

entities.name: React
entities.description: React is a frontend framework that can be connected to Yao via REST API for advanced frontend needs.

entities.name: Vue
entities.description: Vue is a frontend framework that can be connected to Yao via REST API for advanced frontend needs.

relationships.description: Mobile App Client uses Yao as a backend service.
SUI template engine is a part of Yao 0.10.4.
React framework can be connected to Yao via REST API.
Vue framework can be connected to Yao via REST API.
TypeScript processes run in the V8 engine.
Go is used for high-performance processes in Yao.
Yao Process is an atomic function that runs in the Yao Runtime.
